white"><li class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup mb-16 pl-12 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1">A truly portable Sonos speaker</li><li class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup mb-16 pl-12 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1">Supports AirPlay 2, Alexa, and Google Assistant</li><li class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup mb-16 pl-12 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1">Rugged design that can endure the elements</li><li class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup mb-16 pl-12 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1">Wireless charging</li></ul></div><div class="border-t border-franklin pt-16 md:pt-0 [&amp;&gt;p]:mb-8 [&amp;&gt;ul&gt;li]:mb-6 [&amp;&gt;ul&gt;li]:leading-140 [&amp;&gt;ul]:my-0  [&amp;&gt;ul]:mb-16 [&amp;&gt;ul]:py-0 md:[&amp;&gt;ul]:mb-0 [&amp;_*]:font-polysans-mono  [&amp;_*]:text-14 [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black [&amp;_li]:marker:text-franklin [&amp;_p]:font-light [&amp;_strong]:font-medium [&amp;_ul]:font-light md:w-1/2 md:border-t-0 md:first:border-r md:first:pr-16 md:last:pl-16"><h3 class="mb-8 font-polysans-mono font-medium uppercase leading-140 tracking-12">The Bad</h3><ul class="duet--article--unordered-list my-20 list-disc pl-18 marker:text-blurple/100 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white"><li class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup mb-16 pl-12 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1">Bass is limited by form factor</li><li class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup mb-16 pl-12 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1">No stereo pairing over Bluetooth</li><li class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup mb-16 pl-12 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1">10-hour battery life falls short of other speakers</li><li class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup mb-16 pl-12 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1">Sonos app can be buggy on Wi-Fi networks that aren’t yours</li></ul></div></div><div class="flex w-full flex-col items-center px-24 md:flex-row md:flex-wrap md:justify-center md:px-0"><a href="https://www.anrdoezrs.net/links/8836598/type/dlg/sid/vergeSonosRoamReview04062021/https://www.sonos.com/en-us/shop/roam-black.html" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" data-item-id="9560" class="m-8 mb-12 flex w-full items-center justify-center rounded-sm border border-blurple p-8 text-center font-polysans-mono text-11 font-medium uppercase tracking-12 text-blurple shadow-[3px_4px] transition-all duration-[.1s] ease-in-out hover:shadow-[5px_6px] sm:max-w-[250px]">$169 at Sonos</a><a href="https://go.redirectingat.com/?xs=1&amp;id=1025X1701640&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhphotovideo.com%2Fc%2Fproduct%2F1629037-REG%2Fsonos_roam1us1blk_roam_black.html" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" data-item-id="9560" class="m-8 mb-12 flex w-full items-center justify-center rounded-sm border border-blurple p-8 text-center font-polysans-mono text-11 font-medium uppercase tracking-12 text-blurple shadow-[3px_4px] transition-all duration-[.1s] ease-in-out hover:shadow-[5px_6px] sm:max-w-[250px]">$169 at B&amp;H Photo</a><a href="https://shop-links.co/1736948485616538467" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" data-item-id="9560" class="m-8 mb-12 flex w-full items-center justify-center rounded-sm border border-blurple p-8 text-center font-polysans-mono text-11 font-medium uppercase tracking-12 text-blurple shadow-[3px_4px] transition-all duration-[.1s] ease-in-out hover:shadow-[5px_6px] sm:max-w-[250px]">$169 at Best Buy</a></div></aside><div class="mb-40 flex justify-center font-polysans-mono text-12 font-light text-blurple dark:text-franklin"><a title="How we rate and review products" class="border-b" href="/pages/how-we-rate">How we rate and review products</a></div></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">At 6.61 inches tall, the Roam actually stands shorter than popular Bluetooth speakers like the UE Boom 3 and JBL Flip 5. And at under a pound, it’s lightweight enough to toss into your backpack or tote. The Boom is bigger all around: you could pretty much fit the Roam right inside it. UE’s Megaboom 3 and the new JBL Charge 5 both increase the size advantage further, and they’re still close to the Roam in price. Going up from there, you get to the real giants like the UE Megablast. For this review, I’ll keep it simple and focus on speakers that resemble the Roam in size.</p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><div class="duet--article--article-body-component clear-both block w-full md:ml-[-100px] md:w-outdent"><div class="duet--article--image-group-two-up my-40"><div class="sm:flex sm:flex-row"><div class="mb-20 w-full sm:mb-0 sm:mr-20 sm:w-1/2"><div class="transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out"><div class="fixed inset-0 h-[110vh] w-full bg-white transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out z-[-1] cursor-default opacity-0" role="button" aria-label="Close" tabindex="0"></div><div role="button" aria-label="Zoom" tabindex="0" class="visible z-30 w-full origin-center transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out cursor-zoom-in"><div class="relative transition duration-75 ease-in-out p-0"><div class=""><div class=""><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:relative"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;widt